Culture of Greece

 

Greece is well known for its vast culture. Ancient Greece has influenced many world architectural movements along centuries. The architectural style of Greece is divided into many periods due to its diversity. You can see samples of the architecture in Greece with a simple walk in the center of Athens, even the Cycladic one, but Architecture isn't the only thing it is known for. Greece is considered to be one of the cradles of modern culture. 

Greece is known for its mathematical, scientific, and philosophical contributions. Along with the origin of the oldest sporting event the Olympics.

Temple of Artemis

Temple of Artemis, also called  Artemesium, the temple at Ephesus, now in western Turkey, was one of the Seven Wonders of the World. Artemesium was famous not only for its great size, over 350 by 180 feet (about 110 by 55 meters) but also for the works of art that decorated it.

The original statue of Artemis was made of gold, ebony, silver, and black stone. 

 

 

The Parthenon

 Parthenon is a temple that is on the hill of Acropolis in Athens. It was dedicated to the goddess Athena Parthenon.

The temple is considered to be the very culmination of the development of the Doric Order,

the building is 101.34 feet (30.89 meters) wide and 228.14 feet (69.54 meters) long.

The temple known as the Parthenon was built on the Acropolis of Athens between 447 and 438 B.CE.

 

 

 

 

                            Philosophy

Greek defined the word philosophy as the love of wisdom.

They divided the word into two halves and said that Philo means to love and sophy means wisdom. And also said that it is the study of the most basic and profound matters of human existence. The first philosopher of Greek was Aristotle who studied the logic of science and discovered the Pythagoras theorem. 

Mathematical and Scientific Contributions

Greek was the first one on the whole planet who studied medicine from scientific knowledge. The word science is been developed by a Greek word known as ‘episteme’. The Greeks researched space and found out about the whole solar system and Many ancient Greek intellectuals excelled in mathematics, physics, and astronomy.

Aristotle was the first philosopher who developed a systematic study of logic, an early form of evolution was taught by such figures of Greek philosophy as Anaximander and Empedocles, and Pythagoras' mathematical theorem is still used today to introduce the idea of the earth as a globe. It is thanks to these developments the best computer science university is found in Greece.

 

Literature

The literature of Greece began with two great epics the Iliad and the Odyssey .

 

The Greek literature is divided into 3 types

  • Archanic,
  • Classical,
  • Hellenistic.

5 qualities were

  • Epic poetry
  • lyrical poetry
  • comedic dramas
  • tragedies,
  • philosophies
  • historical writings.​

Festivals

Like in all country festivals are celebrated, in Greece also different types of festivals are celebrated.

Some festivals that are famous in the world are Easter is by far the biggest event of the year, celebrated everywhere with candlelit street processions, midnight fireworks and spit-roasted lamb. Some islands are renowned for their unique Easter festivities. Easter week, or Holy Week, is marked by different events each day.

Greek Independence Day, national holiday celebrated annually in Greece on March 25, commemorating the start of the War of Greek Independence in 1821.

 On August 3, seventy-seven archaeological sites, monuments and museums across Greece will host free cultural events. This includes free admission to concerts, theatrical performances, dance performances, poetic recitations, documentary screenings, art exhibitions and stargazing events.​
